{"id":"el-16w","type":"document","createdAt":"2026-03-10T23:25:50.700Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-11T00:01:18.220Z","createdBy":"el-0000","tags":[],"metadata":{"purpose":"document-directory"},"title":"Documentation Directory","contentType":"markdown","content":"# Documentation Directory\n\nIndex of all workspace documents.\n\n## Specs\n\n- **el-3rm** - System Architecture: Complete architecture overview of the Checker health-monitoring system (data flow, components, DB schema, patterns, branch status)\n\n## References\n\n- **el-3ma** - Slack Interactive Endpoint: Reference for POST /api/slack/interactive endpoint (button clicks, signature verification, silence/ack actions)\n\n## Decision Log\n\n(none yet)\n\n## How-To\n\n- **el-3os** - Slack App Setup Guide: How to set up the Checker Slack App integration (OAuth scopes, interactivity, slash commands, silence feature, troubleshooting)","version":5,"previousVersionId":"el-16w","category":"reference","status":"active","immutable":false}
{"id":"el-3ma","type":"document","createdAt":"2026-03-11T00:01:07.301Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-11T00:01:07.301Z","createdBy":"el-0000","tags":[],"metadata":{},"title":"Slack Interactive Endpoint","contentType":"markdown","content":"# Slack Interactive Endpoint\n\nReference documentation for the POST /api/slack/interactive endpoint that handles button clicks from Slack alert messages.\n\n## Endpoint\n\n**POST** `/api/slack/interactive`\n\nHandles Slack interactive message payloads (button clicks). Slack sends these when users click action buttons on alert messages.\n\n## Request Format\n\nSlack sends interactive payloads as `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` with a single `payload` field containing URL-encoded JSON.\n\n## Authentication\n\nEvery request is verified using HMAC-SHA256 signature verification:\n1. Extract `X-Slack-Request-Timestamp` and `X-Slack-Signature` headers\n2. Reject if timestamp is older than 5 minutes (replay protection)\n3. Compute: `HMAC-SHA256(signing_secret, \\\"v0:{timestamp}:{request_body}\\\")`\n4. Compare with `X-Slack-Signature` using timing-safe comparison\n5. Return 401 Unauthorized if verification fails\n\nImplementation: `internal/web.VerifySlackSignature()`\n\n## Supported Actions\n\n### silence_check (action_id: \\\"silence_check\\\")\n- **Value**: Check UUID (from button value)\n- **Creates**: `AlertSilence` with scope=\\\"check\\\", target=UUID, duration=1h\n- **Posts**: Thread reply with silence confirmation via `SlackClient.SendSilenceConfirmation()`\n- **Updates**: Original message to show \\\"Silenced\\\" badge, removes action buttons\n\n### silence_project (action_id: \\\"silence_project\\\")\n- **Value**: Project name (from button value)\n- **Creates**: `AlertSilence` with scope=\\\"project\\\", target=project name, duration=1h\n- **Posts**: Thread reply with silence confirmation\n- **Updates**: Original message to show \\\"Silenced\\\" badge, removes action buttons\n\n### ack_alert (action_id: \\\"ack_alert\\\")\n- **Value**: Check UUID\n- **Posts**: Thread reply with \\\"Acknowledged by @user\\\" message\n- **Updates**: Original message to show \\\"Acknowledged\\\" badge, removes action buttons\n\n## Response\n\nAlways returns 200 OK within 3 seconds (Slack timeout). Processing errors are logged but do not prevent the 200 response to avoid Slack retries.\n\n## Architecture\n\n- **Handler**: `internal/web.SlackInteractiveHandler`\n- **Route registration**: `web/web.go` in `Serve()`\n- **Dependencies**: `internal/slack.SlackClient` (message updates), `internal/db.Repository` (silence persistence)\n- **Wiring**: `cmd/main_checker.go` passes SlackClient and Repository to `web.SetSlackClient()` and `web.SetRepository()`\n\n## Related\n\n- Alert Block Kit blocks with action buttons: `internal/slack/blocks.go` (`BuildAlertBlocks`)\n- Silenced/Acknowledged message blocks: `BuildSilencedOriginalBlocks`, `BuildAcknowledgedOriginalBlocks`\n- Slash command handler: `slack/interactions.go` (separate endpoint at `/api/slack/commands`)\n- DB silence operations: `internal/db/repository.go`","version":1,"previousVersionId":null,"category":"reference","status":"active","immutable":false}
